  "title": "with even feet",
  "sourceFile": "Burbank_notes/evenfeet_N.htm",
  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>with even\n        feet</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>Cf. \"Slowly\" in the previous\n        stanza. Apart from indicating the steady and inevitable\n        approach of the horses, the line might also be a\n        reference to Emily Dickinson: \" We trust, in plumed\n        procession, / For such the angels go, / Rank after rank,\n        with even feet / And uniforms of snow.</font>\"\n        (Life, XVI) - that is, if he'd ever read her. But he says\n        he hasn't. </p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Life_XVI_ED.htm\">Life,\n                XVI</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Life_XVI_ED.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>The War</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sir Ferdinand Klein</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "with even feet Cf. \"Slowly\" in the previous stanza. Apart from indicating the steady and inevitable approach of the horses, the line might also be a reference to Emily Dickinson: \" We trust, in plumed procession, / For such the angels go, / Rank after rank, with even feet / And uniforms of snow. \" (Life, XVI) - that is, if he'd ever read her. But he says he hasn't. reference topics Life, XVI The War Sir Ferdinand Klein back to \"Burbank\"",
